mesa: force Zink for the external-Vulkan linked swrast provider

Why: Xorg names its indirect software DRI provider "swrast" even when the
Gallium implementation behind that provider is Zink.  With Zink as the only
compiled Gallium driver, Mesa's software pipe-loader otherwise tries an empty
default driver name and never reaches zink_create_screen().

What: when the artifact-specific XVFB_STATIC_EXTERNAL_VULKAN define is set,
ignore GALLIUM_DRIVER and select only Zink.  No llvmpipe or softpipe code is
compiled into this variant, so there is deliberately no software GL fallback.

diff --git a/src/gallium/auxiliary/target-helpers/sw_helper.h b/src/gallium/auxiliary/target-helpers/sw_helper.h
--- a/src/gallium/auxiliary/target-helpers/sw_helper.h
+++ b/src/gallium/auxiliary/target-helpers/sw_helper.h
@@ -73,8 +73,12 @@ sw_screen_create_vk(struct sw_winsys *winsys, const struct pipe_screen_config *c
 {
    UNUSED bool only_sw = debug_get_bool_option("LIBGL_ALWAYS_SOFTWARE", false);
    const char *drivers[] = {
+#if defined(XVFB_STATIC_EXTERNAL_VULKAN) && defined(GALLIUM_ZINK)
+      "zink",
+#else
       (sw_vk ? "" : debug_get_option("GALLIUM_DRIVER", "")),
+#endif
 #if defined(GALLIUM_D3D12)
       (sw_vk || only_sw) ? "" : "d3d12",
 #endif
